obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (27970)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27970&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called ^3[the Armed Forces (Special Powers)`
  line `Act, 1958.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) It extends to the whole of the States of ^1[^2[Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya,`
  line `Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura.]]]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 34 of 1986, s. 40, for "Meghalaya, Nagaland and Tripura and the Union territories of Arunachal Pradesh and`
  line `Mizoram" (w.e.f. 20-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 69 of 1986, s. 43, for "Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura and the Union territory`
  line `of Arunachal Pradesh" (w.e.f. 20-2-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 1972, s. 3, for "the Armed Forces (Assam and Manipur) Special Powers Act, 1958" (w.e.f. 5-4-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3,ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-4-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27971)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27971&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "armed forces" means the military forces and the air forces operating as land forces, and`
  line `includes any other armed forces of the Union so operating;`
  line
  line `(b) "disturbed area" means an area which is for the time being declared by notification under`
  line `section 3 to be a disturbed area;`
  line
  line `(c) all other words and expressions used herein, but not defined and defined in the Air Force`
  line `Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), shall have the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27972)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to declare areas to be disturbed areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27972&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Power to declare areas to be disturbed areas.If, in relation to any State or Union`
  line `territory to which this Act extends, the Governor of that State or the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory or the Central Government, in either case, is of the opinion that the whole or any part of such`
  line `State or Union territory, as the case may be, is in such a disturbed or dangerous condition that the use`
  line `of armed forces in aid of the civil power is necessary, the Governor of that State or the Administrator`
  line `of that Union territory or the Central Government, as the case may be, may, by notification* in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare the whole or such part of such State or Union territory to be a disturbed`
  line area.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 3 (w.e.f. 5-4-1972).`
  line `*Central Government declares whole of the State of Nagaland to be disturbed area for a period of six months with effect from 30th December, 2021.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (27973)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Special powers of the armed forces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27973&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any commissioned officer, warrant officer,`
  line `non-commissioned officer or any other person of equivalent rank in the armed forces may, in a`
  line `disturbed area,―`
  line
  line `(a) if he is of opinion that it is necessary so to do for the maintenance of public order, after`
  line `giving such due warning as he may consider necessary, fire upon or otherwise use force, even to`
  line `the causing of death, against any person who is acting in contravention of any law or order for the`
  line `time being in force in the disturbed area prohibiting the assembly of five or more persons or the`
  line `carrying of weapons or of things capable of being used as weapons or of fire-arms, ammunition or`
  line `explosive substances;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of opinion that it is necessary so to do, destroy any arms dump, prepared or`
  line `fortified position or shelter from which armed attacks are made or are likely to be made or are`
  line `attempted to be made, or any structure used as a training camp for armed volunteers or utilised as`
  line `a hide-out by armed gangs or absconders wanted for any offence;`
  line
  line `(c) arrest, without warrant, any person who has committed a cognizable offence or against`
  line `whom a reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed or is about to commit a cognizable`
  line `offence and may use such force as may be necessary to effect the arrest;`
  line
  line `(d) enter and search without warrant any premises to make any such arrest as aforesaid or to`
  line `recover any person believed to be wrongfully restrained or confined or any property reasonably`
  line `suspected to be stolen property or any arms, ammunition or explosive substances believed to be`
  line `unlawfully kept in such premises, and may for that purpose use such force as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (27974)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Arrested persons to be made over to the police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27974&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any person arrested and taken into custody`
  line `under this Act shall be made over to the officer in charge of the nearest police station with the least`
  line `possible delay, together with a report of the circumstances occasioning the arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (27975)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Protection to persons acting under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27975&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution, suit or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `be instituted, except with the previous sanction of the Central Government, against any person in`
  line `respect of anything done or purported to be done in exercise of the powers conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (27976)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490&sectionId=27976&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00003_195828_1517807319490
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal and Saving.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1960 (58 of 1960), s. 2 and the`
  line `First Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
